<br>
There are 5 sets spells. Each line summons a magic lore no-rent item with some AC, health, and mana. Item effects do not stack (so you can't wear a ruby and opal bracelet together for double effect). All pieces are wearable by the priest, hybrid, and caster classes. Recommended levels are usually four or five levels below the spell scribing requirement for the mage. If the piece is given to a lower level character, the stats on the item will drop; I don't know if the percentages granted are modified as well.<br>
<br>
The spell lines are:<br>
Summon Jade/Opal/Ruby Bracelet at levels 20/ 44/ 54<br>
Summon Brass/Silver/Golden Choker at levels 4/24/50<br>
Summon Tarnished/Shiny/Brilliant Bauble at levels 12/34/52<br>
Summon Tiny/Twisted/Studded Ring at levels 16/39/53<br>
Summon Linen/Leather/Silken Mantle at levels 8/29/51<br>
<br>
Tavee's mantles increases the duration of spells up to 15%. It may be currently bugged, as that it only works on beneficial spells you cast on yourself. Not known whether percentage is set.<br>
<br>
Jedah's chokers currently reduce reagent usage, such as cloudy stones of Veeshan needed for the Plane of Sky port. It may be bugged, as that the spdat lists the effect as decreasing mana costs by 15%.<br>
<br>
Jolum's baubles (earrings) decrease aggro generated by casting spells by 15%. Since quantifying aggro is hard to do, this effect may be bugged as well. Unknown whether this is a random or set percentage.<br>
<br>
Naki's rings reduce casting time up to 15%. I believe this is a set percentage. You can inspect your spellbook, or right click the spell gems, to see the modified casting time.<br>
<br>
Gallenite's bracelets increases the damage done by a spell up to 20%. Currently doesn't work with rain spells or pbaoe spells, but apparently works with nuke items such as the Boots of Bladecalling. Effect is a random percentage.<br>
<br>
<br>
